article.description: Blake Francis had 21 points as Richmond topped Duquesne 73-62 on Friday night.
article.headline: Francis scores 21 to carry Richmond over Duquesne 73-62
article.linkText: Francis scores 21 to carry Richmond over Duquesne 73-62
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Blake Francis had 21 points as Richmond topped Duquesne 73-62 on Friday night. Grant Golden had 13 points for Richmond (24-7, 14-4 Atlantic 10 Conference), which earned its fourth straight victory. Nick Sherod added 13 points. Nathan Cayo had 11 points. Tavian Dunn-Martin had 17 points for the Dukes (21-9, 11-7). Baylee Steele added 12 points. Michael Hughes had 10 points. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
